Lines.Comment: As if talking down to a child.
Alt: You need to place that on a vespene geyser.
You think you can build there?
Can't build there. Look where you're building!
Don't let your supply get blocked.
Not enough gas! Gas! Gas! Gas!
You should always inspect the gas!
Be aware of your gas twenty-four seven.
Can't make them work without mineral.
Can't land there, there's something below.
You think you can land there?
What are you doing? Can't land there.
You should build a geyser first!
Enemies are attacking our base! Time for a perfect defense!
You know the pain of SCV?
Your ally's being attacked and you just stand there?!
No nukes... No nukes... No nukes!
Nuke! Nuke! Nuke! Nuke! Look for it!
Upgrade complete. But don't overestimate your self!
We launch Nuke, we win even if we lose!
Allies are being attacked. You're not gonna just stand there and watch.
Allies are being attacked, you can't just stare.
Your ally's base is under attack!
Your ally's base is under attack! Focus!
Let's sweep some minerals with MULE!
Salvage done. Hope you know what you're doing.
That mineral field's been mined out... we lost?
You do have an expansion, right?
Let's pause only when it's really necessary!
You're at max supply! Time to fight seriously!
Ready for the battle now. Let the battle begin!
You think you can build there?
Could you please warp where you can?
Your Pylon is under attack. Prevent the blackout!
That needs to build in a power field.
You know what power field, right? Build inside.
Warp in complete! This is why we play Protoss.
You can't do that. First time playing Zerg?
You know how the overlords look like?
Drones are our future. Protect them!
A creep tumors are under attack.
Protect the creep tumors. You spent so long spreading those!
Your creep tumors are under attack! Think of a poor Queen!
Need a creep for that. You know what creep is, right?
If you want to build anywhere, play Terran.
No, not there. On the creep.
No, not there. You should build on the creep.
Dispassionately, no negative or positive opinion
Second portion is whispered so that the voices can't hear.
Imitating the classic default line, then chuckling about it
Ten through six are spoken very quickly.
Translation: Until we both meet Adun [in death].
The zerg are often referred to as
Sardonically pleased that her long-time enemies cannot grow larger in number.
This line imitates the famous default line; intent is to poke fun at it in a mocking way
